  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0d9c\u0db8\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0da2\u0db4\u0db1\u0dca \u0db8\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dcf\u0da7 \u0dc3\u0db8\u0dd4 \u0daf\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Prime Minister bids farewell to Japanese friend",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Prime Minister Ranil Wickramasinghe visited the Japanese Embassy in Sri Lanka and expressed his condolences today (12) on the death of former Prime Minister Shinsho Abe.",
        "The former Prime Minister of Japan Mr. Shinzo Abe is a long-term political friend of Prime Minister Mr. Ranil Wickremesinghe. The Prime Minister's Office states that when Mr. Ranil Wickremesinghe was the Prime Minister of Sri Lanka, Mr. Shinsho Abe as the Prime Minister of Japan had a friendly policy with Sri Lanka.",
        "The former Prime Minister of Japan was killed in a gun attack on the 8th while he was engaged in a political activity in Nara, Japan.",
        "Mr. Mishukoshi Hideki, the Japanese Ambassador to Sri Lanka also participated in the event where Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe paid his last respects to the former Prime Minister of Japan."
      ],
